# Issue implementation flow (project issues)

When you are asked to **implement a project issue**, **pick an issue from the project**, or **work through the issue workflow**, follow the flow in this document step by step:

**[docs/issue-implementation-flow.md](docs/issue-implementation-flow.md)**

That flow covers: prerequisites (e.g. `gh auth status`), picking only **Ready** + **ai-friendly** issues, creating the branch (prefer `gh issue develop`, then fallback to manual), setting status to In progress, implementation plan (including **link to the GitHub issue**), implementation and commits (one per step if multistep), and PR with structured description and `Closes #N`.

Do not skip steps. When in doubt, open the doc and follow it.

