## Set issue Status to "In progress" (after creating the branch)

Right after creating and checking out the branch for the issue (via `gh issue develop` or manually), set that issue's **project Status to "In progress"**. Only for issues on the **ReAItyCheck project** (project 2, owner @me).

1. Note the **issue number** (e.g. `3`).
2. Resolve the **project item ID** (replace `3` with the issue number):
   ```bash
   ITEM_ID=$(gh project item-list 2 --owner @me -L 100 --format json | jq -r '.items[] | select(.content.number == 3) | .id')
   ```
3. Set the item's Status to **In progress**:
   ```bash
   gh project item-edit --id "$ITEM_ID" --project-id PVT_kwHOAqmy8c4BPKom --field-id PVTSSF_lAHOAqmy8c4BPKomzg9p7fs --single-select-option-id 47fc9ee4
   ```

**ReAItyCheck project IDs:** Project `PVT_kwHOAqmy8c4BPKom`, Status field `PVTSSF_lAHOAqmy8c4BPKomzg9p7fs`, "In progress" option `47fc9ee4`. Requires `gh` and network.
